1. Software Architecture
System Architecture
1.	Citizen registers an account (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend validates input (email uniqueness, password format) 
’āś	Backend encrypts password 
’āś	Data stored in the Users table 
’āś	Citizen account created successfully 
2.	Citizen logs into the system (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend verifies email and password 
’āś	Backend checks encrypted password in Users table 
’āś	If valid, session is created 
’āś	Citizen is redirected to dashboard 
3.	Citizen browses sports facilities (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend queries the Facilities table 
’āś	Backend returns list of facilities 
’āś	Citizen sees available facilities with details 
4.	Citizen checks facility availability (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend queries: 
o	facility_schedules table (working hours) 
o	bookings table (existing reservations)
’āś	Backend calculates available time slots 
’āś	Backend returns available slots 
’āś	Citizen sees real-time availability 
5.	Citizen books a facility (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend validates citizen session and selected time slot 
’āś	Backend checks for conflicts in Bookings table 
’āś	If slot is free:
o	Booking is created 
o	Stored in Bookings table
’āś	Confirmation sent to citizen 
6.	Citizen modifies a booking (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend verifies booking ownership 
’āś	Backend checks new time slot availability 
’āś	If valid: 
o	Booking is updated in Bookings table
’āś	Updated confirmation returned 
7.	Citizen cancels a booking (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend verifies booking 
’āś	Booking status updated to cancelled in Bookings table 
’āś	Slot becomes available again 
8.	System prevents double booking (Backend) 
’āś	When booking request is received 
’āś	Backend checks existing records in Bookings table 
’āś	Unique constraint ensures no duplicate time slot per facility 
’āś	If conflict found 
’āś	Booking rejected 
’āś	Error returned to citizen 
9.	Citizen receives booking notifications (Backend) 
’āś	After booking action 
’āś	Backend triggers notification service 
’āś	Confirmation/reminder sent to citizen (email or system notification) 
10.	Administrator adds or manages facilities (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend verifies admin role 
’āś	Backend inserts/updates/deletes data in Facilities table 
’āś	Changes saved 
’āś	Updated facilities visible to citizens 
11.	Administrator manages citizens (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend checks admin privileges 
’āś	Backend updates citizen roles or data in Users table 
’āś	Changes applied successfully 
12.	Administrator views reports and statistics (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend queries Bookings, Users, and Facilities tables 
’āś	Aggregated data returned 
’āś	Reports displayed 
13.	Facility staff verifies bookings (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend validates staff role 
’āś	Backend updates booking status (verified) in Bookings table 
’āś	Booking marked as confirmed 
14.	Facility staff views daily schedule (Frontend) 
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend queries Bookings table filtered by date and facility 
’āś	Backend returns schedule 
’āś	Staff sees daily bookings 
15.	Citizen makes payment (Frontend)
’āś	Request goes to Backend 
’āś	Backend processes payment 
’āś	Payment details stored in Payments table 
’āś	Booking updated with payment status 

